08/04/2005
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The foreign ministry announced that Croatia will host this year's Crans Montana Forum from 13 April until 15 April in Zagreb. 
Between 400 and 500 participants from 20 countries are expected to attend the event, titled "European Prospects and Regional Co-operation". 
Prime Minister Ivo Sanader has invited all his Southeast European counterparts to an informal meeting on the sidelines. 
The forum will be the largest political and economic event in Croatia this year. 
(HINA - 07/04/05)
